https://www.turnermotorsport.com/p-372289-e39-18-m-parallel-style-37-wheel-set/,https://3a663eb0fef48c6d2d60-a88f8ebfcdb877ad223e888bfcb7f7ec.ssl.cf1.rackcdn.com/246104_x300.jpg,"E39 18"" M Parallel Style 37 Wheel Set",https://c1521972.ssl.cf0.rackcdn.com/img/brands/Genuine%20BMW.gif,372289,3611222963540,In Stock,"$2,485.38",Add to Cart,,https://www.turnermotorsport.com/c-329-bmw-original-bmw-wheels-and-wheel-upgrades#,"For many people, the M Parallel wheels are some of the best-looking wheels that BMW ever released. They have become very popular as retrofit wheels on many other BMW models - from the E28 to the E90. Not a complicated wheel design, the clean split-5 spoke is simple and sporty. These wheels are made in a very low offset with an exaggerated front-rear stagger -- 18x8.0 ET20 in the front and 18x9.0 ET24 in the rear.  The rear wheel has a generous outer lip. These wheels have become a favorite restomod upgrade for E31, E34, and other E38 models. We have even seen them on E46 M3 and E90s. This set uses the wheels from the E39 chassis and have a 74.0mm center bore. Wheel centering rings will be required for non-E39 fitments (included). These are a direct fit for all E39 models.",,,"As with any wheel retrofit, particular attention must be paid to tire sizes, ride height, and alignment settings. We cannot guarantee wheel fitment for every application. Careful consideration of wheel width, offset and tire sizing must be observed when choosing and installing wheels. Adding different or larger wheels may lead to rubbing on suspension components or bodywork. Wheel spacers, new alignment settings, fender modifications, or other adjustments may be required. Retrofitting wheels from one chassis to another may not be compatible with your TPMS system (new TPMS or a TPMS emulator may be requried). For additional resources on wheel fitments,  or give us a call or e-mail.",

Since these wheels are very common with the stance/lowered crowd you may have seen them on some unusual fitments. Since we don't know what modifications were done and what tire sizes were used to make them fit on stanced cars, we cannot guarantee fitment on all models. We have selected chassis where these wheels should fit with minimal issues. Careful consideration of wheel width, offset and tire sizing must be observed when choosing and installing wheels. Adding different or larger wheels may lead to rubbing on suspension components or bodywork. Wheel spacers, new alignment settings, fender modifications, or other adjustments may be required. Retrofitting wheels from one chassis to another may not be compatible with your TPMS system (new TPMS or a TPMS emulator may be requried). column2: ,https://www.turnermotorsport.com/c-329-bmw-original-bmw-wheels-and-wheel-upgrades?No=50&Nrpp=50#,For many people, the M Parallel wheels are some of the best-looking wheels that BMW ever released. They have become very popular as retrofit wheels on many other BMW models - from the E28 to the E90. Not a complicated wheel design, the clean split-5 spoke is simple and sporty. These wheels are made in a very low offset with an exaggerated front-rear stagger -- 18x8.0 ET13 in the front and 18x9.5 ET25 in the rear.  The rear wheel has a generous outer lip. These wheels have become a favorite restomod upgrade for E31, E34, and other E38 models. We have even seen them on E46 M3 and E90s. This wheel set uses the M Parallels from the E38 7-series so they have the correct 72.6mm center bore (no wheel centering rings are required). The offsets and rear wheel width are different compared to the E34 M Parallel set we also offer.",,,"Careful consideration of wheel width, offset and tire sizing must be observed when choosing and installing wheels. Adding different or larger wheels may lead to rubbing on suspension components or bodywork. Wheel spacers, new alignment settings, fender modifications, or other adjustments may be required. Retrofitting wheels from one chassis to another may not be compatible with your TPMS system (new TPMS or a TPMS emulator may be requried). For additional resources on wheel fitments,  or give us a call or e-mail.","window.productHasAppDesc = window.productHasAppDesc || {}

,https://www.turnermotorsport.com/c-329-bmw-original-bmw-wheels-and-wheel-upgrades?No=200&Nrpp=50#,For many people, the M Parallel wheels are some of the best-looking wheels that BMW ever released. They have become very popular as retrofit wheels on many other BMW models - from the E28 to the E90. Not a complicated wheel design, the clean split-5 spoke is simple and sporty. These wheels are made in a very low offset with an exaggerated front-rear stagger -- 18x8.0 ET20 in the front and 18x9.0 ET22 in the rear.  The rear wheel has a generous outer lip. These wheels have become a favorite restomod upgrade for E31, E34, and other E38 models. We have even seen them on E46 M3 and E90s. This wheel set uses the M Parallels from the E34 M5 so they have the correct 72.6mm center bore (no wheel centering rings are required). The offsets and rear wheel width are different compared to the E38 M Parallel set we also offer.",,,"2 x 18x8.0"" ET20 M Parallel front wheels (BMW #36112227931)","window.productHasAppDesc = window.productHasAppDesc || {}

column2: ,https://www.turnermotorsport.com/c-329-bmw-original-bmw-wheels-and-wheel-upgrades?No=200&Nrpp=50#,In our opinion, the 19"" wheel option for the E46 M3 is one of the best looking wheels to put on this car. BMW went very aggressive yet stayed classy with the optional 19"" M double spoke LA wheels (light alloy). With these wheels, you retain the factory appearance and striking good looks thanks to the polished spokes. These are the actual Genuine BMW wheels - not replicas!! They are the highest quality for finish and the correct Original fit to your E46 M3. This package is for a staggered set of two front and two rear wheels.   Wheel Specs:    19x8.0 / ET 47 offset. BMW part number 36 11 2 229 650    19x9.5 / ET 27 offset. BMW part number 36 11 2 229 660   These wheels will also fit the Z4 M Coupe and M Roadster.    These wheels are a drastic change from the stock appearance and will really set your M apart. The front offset is larger on the M3 wheel by 5mm so you may want to use these with a 5mm or 8mm spacer set. The rear does not need any spacers.   For more information on BMW wheels and wheel info in general,       2001-2006    M3  2003-2008    Z4 M Roadster M Coupe",,,Click here for pictures on the Zpost.com forum.,"window.productHasAppDesc = window.productHasAppDesc || {}

,https://www.turnermotorsport.com/c-329-bmw-original-bmw-wheels-and-wheel-upgrades?No=200&Nrpp=50#,BBS R1C Motorsport Cast Flow Formed light weight race wheel as used on the F22 M235iR customer racing car. This is an 18x10.0"" wheel with an ET24 offset and glossy black finish. Each wheel uses the BBS flow forming technology that creates a strong but light weight wheel - 22.8lbs. The M235iR used this wheel on the front and rear to create a square race wheel set. Not only is there more rubber to put power to the pavement (the race car uses 265/660R-18 racing slicks), but more tire in the front helps minimize understeer and improve turn-in grip. The same wheel size also allows you to rotate tires for better tire life. This is the standard bolt pattern and offset for most BMW M3 models but for the F22 wider fenders flares, such as used on the M235iR, will be needed. The M235iR was set up to use 265/660R-18 racing slicks or a 265/35-18 tire. This wheel is very similar to the BBS R1C.",,,Price is for a set of 4 race wheels.,"window.productHasAppDesc = window.productHasAppDesc || {}
